HEADWORD: Ethereality
<hw>E*the`re*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
being ethereal; etherealness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Something of that <qex>ethereality</qex> of thought and manner
which belonged to Wordsworth's earlier lyrics.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etherealization</ent>⟦br⟧
